#[=======================================================================[.rst:
header-config.cmake
-------------------

header cmake module.
This module sets the following variables in your project:

::

   header_FOUND - true if header found on the system
   header_VERSION - header version in format Major.Minor.Release


Exported targets:

::

If header is found, this module defines the following :prop_tgt:`IMPORTED`
targets. ::
    header::header - the main header only library with header & defs attached.


Suggested usage:

::

    find_package(header)
    find_package(header CONFIG REQUIRED)


The following variables can be set to guide the search for this package:

::

    header_DIR - CMake variable, set to directory containing this Config file
    CMAKE_PREFIX_PATH - CMake variable, set to root directory of this package
    PATH - environment variable, set to bin directory of this package
    CMAKE_DISABLE_FIND_PACKAGE_api - CMake variable, disables find_package(header)
    perhaps to force internal build

#]=======================================================================]
@PACKAGE_INIT@

include(CMakeFindDependencyMacro)

# third library dependency check
find_dependency(absl:log REQUIRED)

include("${CMAKE_CURRENT_LIST_DIR}/header-targets.cmake")
check_required_components(header)
